Thank you for visiting our Philadelphia PA 19154 chiropractic clinic, a five-star, award-winning chiropractic, and rehabilitation center. Seeking out chiropractic therapy for daily aches and pains can improve your long-term quality of life. Our team of doctors in Philadelphia PA 19154 can help you identify the core problem areas and develop a strategy for dealing with your pain.

Chiropractic treatment involves our Philadelphia, PA 19154-based chiropractors applying varying degrees of pressure through a series of spinal manipulations. These manipulations ease the pain you feel by identifying where the pain originates from and appropriately dealing with the issue.

Our Philadelphia, PA 19154-based chiropractic services aim to help ease your long journey through physical therapy and get you back on your feet as quickly as possible.

Dr. Francis McCaffery, DC is a chiropractic neurologist certified by the Pennsylvania State Board of Chiropractic and by the National Board of Chiropractic Examiners. We offer various chiropractic treatment options to help you deal with the issues you currently face. Our chiropractors in Northeast Philadelphia PA 19154 are here to help you at every step to ensure you receive the best treatment possible.

Keeping your body in prime condition to perform the physical activities that modern life requires can be exhausting. That challenge is daunting when simple rest does not soothe every physical ailment that affects us. Chiropractic treatment from Philadelphia, PA 19154’s Academy Injury & Health Center can help!

Incorporating wellness chiropractic care into your health routine can improve your overall quality of life. Our practice provides our clients with chiropractic treatments that address their core and ensure comfort and confidence in their care.

Academy Injury & Health Center’s doctors help realign your spine through a careful series of adjustments and provide you with exercises that aim to strengthen those areas. Our main chiropractic goal is to ensure that your wellness is taken care of and that you are symptom-free by the time you leave our care.

Is chiropractic the right treatment for you? Call our team at Academy Injury & Health Center in Philadelphia PA 19154. We will do our best to help you reach your goals.
